  "prompt": "My Instagram account with 8.5k followers just got hacked into. I've spent the the last hour looking up ways to hack it and trying to get it back and nothing's working. How can I get it back?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that your Instagram account has been hacked. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you recover it:\n\n1. **Secure Your Email and Phone Number**:  \n   - If the hacker changed your associated email or phone number, secure those first. Check your email for notifications from Instagram and follow their instructions.  \n   - Change passwords for any linked accounts (email, phone, etc.) to prevent further access.\n\n2. **Use Instagram\u2019s Account Recovery Tools**:  \n   - Go to the Instagram login page and click \u201cForgot password?\u201d.  \n   - Enter your username, email, or phone number linked to the account.  \n   - Follow the instructions sent to your email or phone to reset your password.\n\n3. **Submit an Identity Verification Form**:  \n   - Visit [Instagram\u2019s Help Center](https://help.instagram.com/) and click \u201cNeed more help?\u201d.  \n   - Select \u201cMy account was hacked\u201d and follow the prompts.  \n   - You may need to provide proof of identity (e.g., a photo of yourself holding a code or government-issued ID) to verify ownership.\n\n4. **Check for Suspicious Activity**:  \n   - Once you regain access, check for unauthorized changes (e.g., linked accounts, profile info, or removed posts).  \n   - Enable **two-factor authentication** (2FA) for added security.\n\n5. **Report the Hack to Instagram**:  \n   - Visit [this link](https://help.instagram.com/contact/606967319425038) to report your hacked account directly to Instagram.\n\n6. **Protect Your Account Moving Forward**:  \n   - Use a strong, unique password and avoid reusing passwords from other sites.  \n   - Regularly review your account\u2019s security settings and linked apps/devices to remove anything suspicious.\n\nIf you\u2019re still unable to recover your account, try reaching out to Instagram\u2019s support team through their official channels or social media platforms like Twitter (@Instagram or @Meta). Be patient, as recovery can take time. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
